 It was a scene that recalled the golden days for Ben Johnson.
 The media were there, as before, chronicling a news conference.
 Johnson was as before, shy and yet brimming with confidence.
 Johnson will at last get his chance to do that.
 And so the questions begin: What can Johnson do when not assisted by performance-enhancing drugs? "Once he returns to the sport, and if he returns a winner, all is forgiven," said Paul Gaines, assistant meet director for the Hamilton Spectator Indoor Games, the Canadian meet to be held Jan. 11 that will mark Johnson's return to competition. "I think that is the attitude the public will display.
